      "comment_id" : 22963873,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Anonymous classes are never static according to the JLS but they can be declared in static scope. When using reflection to ask if such a class is static, ECJ&#39;s generated code says no while javac&#39;s <a href=\"http://ideone.com/cGgs58\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">says yes</a>. Related post <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/758570/is-it-possible-to-make-anonymous-inner-classes-in-java-static\">here</a>."
